And then the next shoe dropped. Dev Kundaliya develops the narrative: Burger King accused of silencing security researcher with copyright claim“Takedown action”The post, titled “We Hacked Burger King,” remained online for less than two days before being taken down following a [DMCA] notice, [alleging] unauthorised use of the “Burger King” trademark, [that] the content promoted illegal activity, spread false information, and damaged the company’s reputation.…BobDaHacker insisted responsible disclosure protocols had been followed, saying flaws had been reported to RBI within an hour of discovery and stressing that no customer data was collected. RBI reportedly fixed the issues the same day, but still pursued takedown action.




